Copyright 1998 The Austin American-Statesman Austin American-Statesman
January 2, 1998
SECTION: Metro/State; Pg. B5
LENGTH: 797 words
HEADLINE: MILESTONES/MILITARY NEWS/KUDOS
BODY :
Army Spec. WILLIAM R. DOBBS, son of William E. and Rebecca C. Dobbs of Austin, has received the Army Commendation Medal. Dobbs is a 1993 graduate of Westwood High School.
Army Pvt. JAMES L. GARNER, son of Beverly D. Trotterof Buda, has graduated from One Station Unit Training at Fort Mcclellan, Anniston, Ala.
Army Pvt. HERMAN E. KEESE, son of Anne E. Keese of Austin, has graduated from One Station Unit Training at Fort Knox, Ky.
Page 7
-
Air Force Airman KATHERINE F. LITTLEWOOD, son of David S. Littlewood and Anne D. Fennell of Austin, has graduated from the communications and navigation apprentice course at Keesler Air Force Base, Biloxi, Miss.
KELLY E. MCKEE, daughter of Randall Mckee and Toni Oyler of Austin, has been designated as a Marine lance corporal with the Headquarters Battalion, Third Marine Division, Okinawa, Japan. McKee is a 1996 graduate of Anderson High School.
Army Cpl. WARREN S. MCLEAN, son of Eugene F. McLean of Mesquite and Betty A. McLean of Austin, has been named noncommissioned officer of the quarter for exemplary duty performance. McLean is a 1986 graduate of Adams High School, Dallas.
Air Force Airman ROBERT A. MCRAE, son of Robert A. McRae of Pflugerville, has graduated from the aerospace apprentice course at Sheppard Air Force Base, Wichita Falls.
Army Pvt. MICHAEL J. MOTTOLO, son of Christine A. Archuletacq of Georgetown, has graduated from One Station Unit Training at the U.S. Army Infantry School, Fort Benning, Columbus, Ga.
Army 2nd Lt. JASON C. PORTER, son of Martin L. Porter of Austin and Doris A. Kosik of Round Rock, has completed the armor officer basic course at Fort Knox, Ky. Porter is a 1997 graduate of the U.S. Army Military Academy, West Point, .N.Y.
. Army Pvt. RYAN J. SHIELD, son of James L. Shield of Austin andBee Bennett of Fort Worth, has graduated from One Stacion Unit Training atthe U.S. Army Infantry School, Fort Benning, Columbus, Ga.
